subject: meta-fii: meta-kudo: Use I2C array definitions in kudo-lib.sh
commitMessage:
meta-fii: meta-kudo: Use I2C array definitions in kudo-lib.sh

Adds the I2C bus and address in array form to kudo-lib.sh, and
replaces the hardcoded values with references across Kudo layer.

Signed-off-by: Charles Boyer <Charles.Boyer@fii-usa.com>
Change-Id: I69bbff444e013e61d7f7fd5051612a6d4adc8ded

Are these hex values or decimals?
The bus values are decimal while the addresses are hexadecimal. I now added a comment with this description.
CI is failing here due to issues found in theses scripts. Please look over https://jenkins.openbmc.org/job/ci-openbmc/distro=ubuntu,label=docker-builder,target=repotest/9233/console

I have project-lib.sh in the exemptions for the run-repotest from https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/51087 and verified that this patchset has it in run-repotest script through basing. Nevertheless, the run-repotest is still analyzing it and so failing CI.
Removed project-lib.sh usage by placing definitions in kudo-lib.sh instead. General shellcheck issues will be fixed in another commit.
